The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Maruti, Tata drag car sales down
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Maruti, Tata drag car sales down
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, Sept. 11: Car sales fell for the second consecutive month in August because of higher interest rates on loans and inflation.         
	Maruti Suzuki and Tata Motors disappointed, while the sales of Hyundai Motor shot up on the back of the success of hatchback i10.         
	Domestic passenger car sales in August stood at 94,584 units against 98,893 units in the same month last year, a fall of 4.36 per cent, according to the figures released by the Society of Indian Automobile Manufacturers.        
	Maruti registered a decline of 10.07 per cent in sales at 46,811 units against 52,055 units in the same month last year. Tata Motors sales fell 10.10 per cent to 12,216 units from 13,588 units in the year-ago period.        
	According to an industry source, Rising interest rates have hit the A1 and A2 segment. Being the market leader, Maruti has the largest presence in both these categories.         
	Marutis sales showed a decline of 32.2 per cent in the A1 segment (Maruti 800). It sold 3,717 units against 5,480 units last year. Sales in the A2 segment comprising the Alto, WagonR, Swift and the Zen declined 9.7 per cent. The company sold 37,667 units against 41,736 units in 2007-08 in the segment.        
	Hyundai posted 34.08 per cent growth at 21,607 units against 16,115 units a year ago.        
	Car companies are still reeling under the pressure of high interest rates. It will take some time before the industry gets on the recovery path.                                                                                                                                     
